sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K557007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is composed of LasBox which can be repressed by LasR/LasI binding and cI which can influence the outcome of toggle switch involved. Thus it helps constructing the negative feedback in BBa_K557008 and works better on a low to medium copy plasmid (pSB3T5) and the two-plasmid system functions well in production of clearly divided colonies.More details could be read on the page of BBa_K557008.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yinghong Lan Siwei Luo
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: BBa_J64800 has been acquired through de novo synthesis and been assembled to the standard part BBa_B0034.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K228237
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The part is RBS->cI->Terminator. K228236 is added to the RBS BBa_B0030 to construct this part. We also have constructed a few similar parts with various RBS, which would make the expression regulation of cI gene more convenient by choosing different parts.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Guosheng Zhang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Built by joining different standardized biobricks together
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The length of RBS part is quite small, so it should be digested to a vector and attached to the cI+Terminator insert.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K228236
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We have attached the cI insert to a terminator vector, which made the next step construction more convenient.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Guosheng Zhang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Built by joining different standardized biobricks together
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The length of terminator part is quite small, so it should be digested to a vector and attached to the cI insert.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cI repressor from E. coli phage lambda (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the cI repressor based on cI repressor from bacteriophage lambda modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein. cI repressor binds to the cI regulator (BBa_R0051).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
References (unparsed) here:

A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000

Octamerization of CI repressor is needed for effective repression of PRM and efficient switching from lysogeny. Ian B. Dodd,1 Alison J. Perkins, Daniel Tsemitsidis, and J. Barry Egan , Genes and Development (Vol 15, No. 22) 3013-3022: 2001

References (unparsed) here:

A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000

Octamerization of CI repressor is needed for effective repression of PRM and efficient switching from lysogeny. Ian B. Dodd,1 Alison J. Perkins, Daniel Tsemitsidis, and J. Barry Egan , Genes and Development (Vol 15, No. 22) 3013-3022: 2001

BBa_C0051 cI repressor is based on the cI repressor from the Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LAA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64800
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is similar to BBa_R0079 but has an added binding site for RHLR/RHLI in between the -35 and -10 region. Thus this promoter is induced by LasR/LasI but repressed by RHLR/RHLi binding.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: laura lavery
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Rust L. et. al., "Analysis of the Pseudomonas aeruginosa Elastase (lasB) Regulatory Region". Journal of Bacteriology, 1996.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There is a 17bp spacer between the -35 and -10 regions and the binding site for RHLR/RHLI is 20bp long. I was able to fit the whole binding site in the spacer region because the last three base pairs of the -35 region and the first three base pairs of the RHLR/RHLI binding site are the same.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
